# EC2[Elastic Cloud Compute]
============================

# What is Compute
=================
1. Compute is nothing but we are asking aws to provide compute resources like Ram,Cpu,Disk.Technically we are asking a virtual server

# Virtual Server
================
1. Virtual Server is a software-based computer that run inside a physical server

* With an EC2 virtual server we can do the below ones
1. We can run applications and Websites
2. We can install any operating systems like Linux or Windows
3. Configure Cpu,Ram and Storage
4. We can scale our resources up or down

# Steps for Creating Instances
==============================
Step-1
======
Click on Launch Instance 
Step-2
======
We have to select the Number of instances 
Eg- 1 Instance i am selecting
Step-3
======
We have to specify the name of the instance
Eg-my-first-instance 
Step-4
======
We have to select operating systems(OS)
Eg-I am selecting Ubuntu after we have to select OS version
Step-5
======
We have to select the Instance type 
Eg- I am selecting T3.Micro
Step-6
======
We have to select Key pair if key is not created click on Create new key pair and login with that key in Putty or Mobaxterm
Step-7
======
Network Setting keep as default
Step-8
======
Configure storage
1x [8]
GiB [gp3]










